            <title>[HTTPCLIENT-1056] Wrong creation of AuthScope object</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HTTPCLIENT-1056</link>
                <project id="12310360" key="HTTPCLIENT">HttpComponents HttpClient</project>
                        <description>Class Name: org.apache.http.client.protocol.RequestAuthCache&lt;br/&gt;
Line #: 118-119&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Issue: Want to create a new Object of AuthScope by passing host name, port and scheme name but due to incorrect constructor call, Getting a object with realm name as scheme name.&lt;br/&gt;
Current Code: Credentials creds = credsProvider.getCredentials(new AuthScope(host.getHostName(), host.getPort(), null, schemeName));</description>
